o entsteht eine genauere und kritische Analyse zu einem Thema, das die Politik immer wieder herausfordert.  aThe ambivalent relationship between politics and violence, although currently explosive, thus far remains abstract and conceptually indistinct in political philosophy. This book draws on different disciplinary and subdisciplinary perspectives over and above political philosophy, for instance considerations from international relations or sociology.In this way, a more accurate and critical analysis emerges on a topic which poses a challenge to politics time and again.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aInternational relationsvCongresses. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophyvCongresses. 0aPolitical violencevCongresses. 0aViolencevCongresses. 4aGewalt. 4aInternationale Beziehungen. 4aKonfliktforschung. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Theorie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aConflict Studies.  aPhilosophy.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitical Theory.  aPolitics.  aViolence.1 aCelikates, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEberl, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlügel-Martinsen, Oliver, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGeis, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuch, Hannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoick, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinsen, Franziska, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartinsen, Franziska, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMartinsen, Oliver Flügel-, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeyer, Katrin, econtr